collectible.name: Scarcity: Water Faction Oldschool Ship
collectible.author: 0xe330dc28b47d73884ad88837aecfee1f49ad7e7b
collectible.description: These were the ships the water faction used before they were called this way. Although the gnomes had powerful machines to cross the ocean, Tilt knew, from the Old Tales of Scarcity, written by the first sailors, that the Atlantis would attack any technological ship they see.Tilt sailed for many months, around Origin City, until he found Fauna Island. In that time, it was empty and it was called the Seahorse Island, given its form, but it was the location under which the Atlantis lived.

Anubis is leading the way. This zumbi fire gnome is part of a horde that was ressurrected to destroy all the chances of Scarcity's citizens of defending themselves. Their bodies are deteriorating, but they are strong and persistent. Created by Egglion and branded by The Philosopher.

collectible.name: Scarcity: Necro, the Dark Faction Leader
collectible.author: 0xe330dc28b47d73884ad88837aecfee1f49ad7e7b
collectible.description: Necro's story is one of the saddest of all Scarcity Tales. He lost his wife in an alchemical accident, doing research, soon after they had a baby. He could not forgive himself for letting her die, and he gathered all the gnomes interested in ressurecting their loved ones to a quest within Flora, in order to find one of the last immortal druids in human form, Klava.

collectible.name: Scarcity: Drog, Leader of the Earth Faction
collectible.author: 0xe330dc28b47d73884ad88837aecfee1f49ad7e7b
collectible.description: Drog, beyond being a miner, was a political philosopher and a statesman. The gnomish grow was faster than the foreseen, after Crisa left the island, and Drog convinced most part of the gnomes left in the island of the unfairness of disconnecting property rights from the social function of property. His left wing thoughts spread through Abundance, and they took the land of the absent gnomes. Drog was aclaimed and everybody had a home, metal and crystals now. Unfortunately, this would not last...

collectible.name: Scarcity: Tilt, Leader of the Water Faction
collectible.author: 0xe330dc28b47d73884ad88837aecfee1f49ad7e7b
collectible.description: Tilt was never a warrior, but a diplomat. His travels through the metaverse always brought good trades for Abundance. The decision to look for the Atlantis was not without reason. For years, the gnomes are trying to boost their super machines with large amounts of energy that could be kept in small crystals. The Atlantis have or at least know where the Diamond of Days is located. Titl wants power to Abundance, and he'll find it in the depths of the ocean. When back Scarcity is what he will find.

collectible.name: Scarcity: Anna, Leader of the Fire Faction
collectible.author: 0xe330dc28b47d73884ad88837aecfee1f49ad7e7b
collectible.description: The legends say that Anna was born from fire and metal. Her mother was making the first sword of Abundance, the Magical Sword of Light, when she gave birth to Anna. This sword was inherited by Anna, and it has secret runes, which her mother taught her to read, about blacksmith's creations. Anna built a generation of blacksmiths gnomes, and she provided all the instruments for mining development and army creation, the foundation of Abundance growth and expansionism.

collectible.name: Scarcity: Crisa, Leader of the Air Faction
collectible.author: 0xe330dc28b47d73884ad88837aecfee1f49ad7e7b
collectible.description: Crisa doesn't like to be called a leader. She thinks democratically, and all of her proposals are debated among the faction. She invented the 1st gnomish air vehicle. It was a collective decision that made the air faction to get the air vehicles to concquer the non minted islands. They thought they could get resources to Abundance before the high population gronwth, which was foreseen for the next 200 years. But to leave Abundance was not a good idea, as Crisa would notice...

collectible.name: Scarcity: Tempus, Leader of the Cyber Faction
collectible.author: 0xe330dc28b47d73884ad88837aecfee1f49ad7e7b
collectible.description: Tempus decided to not go to war. He thought the only way to end the war and defeat the undead was to gather together all the gnomes left from the old factions, and try to come back in time, and forbid the gnomish split. He really developed a time machine, but he is trying to get over the Grandfather Paradox. Abundance will be back again!
